#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:2
msgid "Custom Branding Tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:4
msgid ""
"Use custom branding tools to present a Mattermost experience that is "
"tailored to the branding of your organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:9
msgid "Enable Custom Branding"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:11
msgid ""
"Go to **System Console > Site Configuration > Customization > Enable "
"Custom Branding** (or **System Console > Customization > Custom "
"Branding** in versions prior to 5.12) and set the value to ``true``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:12
msgid ""
"Choose a **Site Name**, upload a **Custom Brand Image**, and enter "
"**Custom Brand Text**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:13
msgid "Click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:15
msgid ""
"Users should see your new custom branding on the login page of your "
"Mattermost server the next time they sign in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:17
msgid ""
"From version 5.16, you can remove the custom brand image by selecting the"
" **X** in the top right corner of the image. To apply the change, choose "
"**Save**. Note that the value must be set to ``true`` in order to perform"
" this step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:19
msgid "More about settings available in **Customer Branding Tools**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:22
msgid "Site Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:23
msgid ""
"Choose the name of your Mattermost site to be shown in the UI. The site "
"name appears in the header and footer of the site login page, team "
"selection page, team creation page, account creation page, email "
"invitations and replaces \"Mattermost\" on the **About** page. Note that "
"the site name applies to the entire site and not just a specific team on "
"the site. The site name is limited to 30 characters or less."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:26
msgid "Custom Branding Image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:27
msgid ""
"Upload a company logo or custom image representative of your site that is"
" displayed on the left side of the site login page. Supported image "
"formats are JPG, PNG, TIFF, and BMP. The recommended image size is "
"200-500px in width and height, and less than 2 MB since it is loaded for "
"every user who logs in on desktop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:30
msgid "Custom Brand Text"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:31
msgid ""
"Write custom text to display your company tagline or a welcome prompt. "
"Custom text will be shown below the custom brand image on the left side "
"of site login page on desktop. You can format this text to a maximum of "
"500 characters using the same `Markdown formatting syntax "
"<http://docs.mattermost.com/help/messaging/formatting-text.html>`__ as "
"used in Mattermost messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:34
msgid "Site Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/administration/branding.rst:35
msgid ""
"Use this field to describe the purpose of your site. The site description"
" is shown below the site name on the login page.  This text defaults to "
"``All team communication in one place, searchable and accessible "
"anywhere``. This text can be a maximum of 1024 characters and is not "
"formatted with Markdown."
msgstr ""

